--GIT Cheat Sheet
Category	Command	Description	Example
Setup	git config --global user.name	Set username	git config --global user.name "John"
	git config --global user.email	Set email	git config --global user.email "john@mail.com"
	git config --list	View configuration	git config --list
Repository	git init	Initialize new repository	git init
	git clone	Clone existing repository	git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
Status & Tracking	git status	Show changed files	git status
	git add file	Add file to staging	git add app.py
	git add .	Add all files	git add .
Commit	git commit -m	Commit staged changes	git commit -m "feat: add login"
Branching	git branch	List branches	git branch
	git branch <name>	Create branch	git branch feature-api
	git checkout <branch>	Switch branch	git checkout feature-api
	git checkout -b <branch>	Create and switch branch	git checkout -b feature-login
	git switch <branch>	Modern way to switch branch	git switch main
Merge	git merge <branch>	Merge branch into current	git merge feature-login
Remote Repository	git remote add origin	Add remote repo	git remote add origin repo_url
	git remote -v	Show remote repos	git remote -v
Push & Pull	git push	Push commits to remote	git push origin main
	git push -u origin	Push and track branch	git push -u origin feature1
	git pull	Pull latest changes	git pull origin main
	git fetch	Download changes only	git fetch
History	git log	Show commit history	git log
	git log --oneline	Short commit history	git log --oneline
	git log --graph	Visual commit graph	git log --graph --oneline
Compare Changes	git diff	Show file differences	git diff
	git show	Show commit details	git show commit_id
	git blame	Show line author	git blame file.py
Undo Changes	git reset file	Unstage file	git reset app.py
	git reset --soft HEAD~1	Undo last commit (keep changes)	git reset --soft HEAD~1
	git reset --hard HEAD~1	Remove last commit completely	git reset --hard HEAD~1
Discard Changes	git checkout -- file	Discard file changes	git checkout -- app.py
	git reset --hard	Remove all local changes	git reset --hard
Stash	git stash	Save changes temporarily	git stash
	git stash pop	Restore stashed changes	git stash pop
	git stash list	Show stashes	git stash list
Tagging	git tag	Create tag	git tag v1.0
	git push origin tag	Push tag	git push origin v1.0


 Most Used Daily Commands (Quick List)
Command	Purpose
git status	Check working directory
git add .	Stage changes
git commit -m "message"	Save changes
git pull	Get latest code
git push	Upload changes
git branch	See branches
git checkout -b branch	Create new branch
